{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, the comparison with the AEiO baseline highlights the benefits of entity-specific instructions on information extraction performance.",
    "Analysis of Figure 3 reveals that G&O-NER consistently boosts precision relative to the One-Step method without significantly affecting recall on average.",
    "It shows that the opportunity to explain its results, facilitated by the CoT process, encourages GPT-3.5 to produce more precise final outputs through self-verification and clean-up.",
    "Ablation Studies To assess the contribution of key elements within our approach, we conduct two straightforward ablation studies: excluding the CoT prompting and omitting the cleanup process.",
    "Results in Table 1 show that the former leads to a 11.87% partial F 1 drop on average and the latter 2.11%."
  ]
}